As all seemed quiet for the moment, Cody let a part of his mind drift as he cautiously moved forward. For a moment, he idly
wondered whether he had ever been in a place like this before. Immediately his thoughts skittered away from the topic,
seizing on the next thing to come to mind, which happened to be the garden he had recently planted. "Hmm," he said.
Hesitantly, he reached out, trying to get a good feel for the walls, and he found himself thinking fervently of nasturtiums.
His concern slipped away, leaving only a faintly lingering unease.
